================================================================================
SERVICENOW TABLES & FIELDS — CSA 2025 NOTES
================================================================================

1) SERVICENOW DATA MODEL (FOUNDATION)
-------------------------------------
• ServiceNow stores data using a database structure.
• Core components:
   - Tables
   - Records
   - Fields

Relationship:
• Table  → collection of records
• Record → single row in a table
• Field  → column storing data for a record

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) TABLES
---------
• A table stores records of similar type.
• Each record represents one entry (row).
• Tables are viewed using:
   - List view (multiple records)
   - Form view (single record)

• Every table has a unique name (technical name).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3) RECORDS
----------
• A record is one row in a table.
• Each record is uniquely identified by:
   - **sys_id** (32-character unique ID)
• sys_id is system-generated and immutable.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4) FIELDS
---------
• Fields are columns in a table.
• Fields store actual data.

COMMON FIELD TYPES:
• String
• Integer
• Boolean (True/False)
• Choice
• Reference
• Date / Date-Time

FIELD ATTRIBUTES:
• Field Label
   - Display name shown to users.
• Field Name
   - Backend name used in scripting.
• Field Value
   - Actual data stored for the record.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5) SYSTEM DEFINITION (ADMIN CONCEPT)
------------------------------------
• Tables and fields are managed under **System Definition**.
• Important concepts:
   - Tables
   - Columns
   - Dictionary entries

• Dictionary defines:
   - Field type
   - Mandatory / Read-only
   - Default value
   - Reference behavior

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6) TABLE RELATIONSHIPS (VERY IMPORTANT)
---------------------------------------
ServiceNow supports three main relationships:

A) ONE-TO-MANY
• One record relates to many records in another table.
• Implemented using **Reference fields**.

Example:
• User (sys_user) → Incident
• One user can be the caller for many incidents.

B) MANY-TO-MANY
• Multiple records in one table relate to multiple records in another.
• Implemented using a **Many-to-Many (M2M) table**.

Example:
• Groups ↔ Roles
• Table: sys_group_has_role

C) TABLE EXTENSION (INHERITANCE)
• A table can extend another table.
• Child table inherits all fields of parent table.

Example:
• task (parent table)
• incident, change, problem (child tables)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7) BASE TABLE vs EXTENDED TABLE
-------------------------------
• Base Table:
   - Not extended from any other table.
   - Can be extended by other tables.

Example:
• task
• cmdb_ci

• Extended Table:
   - Extends another table.
   - Inherits parent fields.

Example:
• incident extends task
• problem extends task

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8) CORE TABLES vs CUSTOM TABLES
-------------------------------
• Core Tables:
   - Provided Out-of-the-Box by ServiceNow.
   - Used by standard applications.

Examples:
• incident
• change_request
• problem
• task

• Custom Tables:
   - Created by admins or developers.
   - Usually start with **u_** (in global scope).

Example:
• u_leave_request
• u_training_tracker

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9) FIELD CREATION & CUSTOMIZATION (CSA LEVEL)
---------------------------------------------
• Admins can add custom fields to core or custom tables.
• Custom fields are stored as dictionary entries.
• Fields can be:
   - Mandatory
   - Read-only
   - Visible / hidden

NOTE:
• Adding a field to a table makes it available for forms & lists.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
10) KEY CSA EXAM TAKEAWAYS
--------------------------
• Data in ServiceNow is stored in tables.
• Tables contain records; records contain fields.
• Every record has a unique sys_id.
• Reference fields create relationships.
• task is a base table.
• incident, change, problem extend task.
• Core tables = OOB, Custom tables = admin-created.
• Dictionary controls field behavior.

================================================================================
END OF TABLES & FIELDS — CSA 2025
================================================================================
